.RE
.B
\fBrecv_chunk(Client :: client()) ->\fR
\fB                    ok |\fR
\fB                    {ok, Bin :: binary()} |\fR
\fB                    {error, Reason :: term()}.\fR

.RS
.LP
Deprecated: ftp:recv_chunk/1 is deprecated; Legacy protocol support will be dropped in OTP-30, use more modern approach for file transfer as for instance SFTP (SSH File Transfer Protocol).
.RE

.br
.RS
.PP
Receives a chunk of the remote file (\fIRemoteFile\fR of \fIrecv_chunk_start\fR). The return values have the following meaning:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIok\fR = the transfer is complete.

.RE

.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fI{ok, Bin}\fR = just another chunk of the file.

.RE

.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fI{error, Reason}\fR = transfer failed.

.RE


